In this update:
Cases in various countries:
Asia
---
India (Chennai, Tamil Nadu)
India (Koraput district, Odisha)
India (Ganjam district, Odisha)
India (Guntur district, Andhra Pradesh)
India (Kolkata, West Bengal)
Pakistan (Karachi, Sindh)
Sri Lanka (national)

******
Cases in various countries:
Asia
---
- India (Chennai, Tamil Nadu). 31 Aug 2012. Doctors say there has been an increase in dengue cases, particularly among children, in the last few months. The Chennai Corporation recorded 329 cases of dengue so far this year [2012], including 299 cases till 25 Aug [2012]. Most children's hospitals in the city say they see at least one suspected case of dengue every day with children coming with complaints of high fever and body ache.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-31/chennai/33520069_1_dengue-death-dengue-shock-syndrome-dengue-cases

[Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and http://healthmap.org/r/1pSH. - Mod.TY]

- India (Koraput district, Odisha). 30 Aug 2012. In southern Odisha, 3 cases have been detected in the tribal dominated Koraput district, health officials said. These cases involve a 19-year-old, an 18-year-old, and a 14-year-old.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-30/bhubaneswar/33498303_1_dengue-menace-separate-dengue-ward-koraput

- India (Ganjam district, Odisha). 28 Aug 2012. Dengue has spread to newer areas in Ganjam district. It was reported from Berhampur and Hinjili towns. With this the number of dengue cases in the district has gone up to 7, said additional district medical officer (public health) LK Rath. He said 3 cases each were reported from Berhampur and Hinjili.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-28/bhubaneswar/33448939_1_dengue-cases-malaria-officer-blood-samples

- India (Guntur district, Andhra Pradesh). 29 Aug 2012. Dengue fever is on the rise in Guntur district and 6 dengue positive cases were registered so far in the district, 2 in Guntur city, and one each in Narasaraopet town, Pedakurapadu, Tadepalli, and Bellamkonda mandals.
http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/cities/regions/vijayawada/6-dengue-cases-detected-guntur-012

- India (Kolkata, West Bengal). 28 Aug 2012. Kolkata is reeling under an outbreak of dengue, 2 people have died and many are flooding hospitals and clinics for treatment.
http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kolkata-dengue-outbreak-claims-2-lives/286078-3-231.html

[No numbers of total dengue cases or DHF cases are given. - Mod.TY]

- Pakistan (Karachi, Sindh). 29 Aug 2012. A total of 157 cases of dengue virus have been reported in Sindh, of which 156 cases were reported in Karachi while one is from Hyderabad.
http://www.brecorder.com/pakistan/general-news/75859.htm

[Maps of Pakistan can be accessed at http://www.mapsofworld.com/pakistan/pakistan-political-map.html and http://healthmap.org/r/1kc-.- Mod.TY]

- Sri Lanka (national). 26 Aug 2012. According to data released by the Health Ministry's Epidemiology Unit, the number of cases stands at 25 679. However, the number of deaths has not been released by the Epidemiology Unit since June this year [2012]. The last update was 75 deaths. Colombo still remains the deadly district with 6299 cases to date, followed by Gampaha with 4556 cases, and Kalutara with 1643 cases. More cases are reported in Kandy and Kurungala as well.
http://www.sundaytimes.lk/120826/news/dengue-death-statistics-withheld-by-health-ministry-10091.html

[Maps of Sri Lanka can be seen at http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/srilanka.pdf and http://healthmap.org/r/1A-B. - Mod.TY]
